text: Keeline is an unincorporated community in Niobrara County, in the U.S. state of Wyoming. ==History== A post office called Keeline was established in 1908, and remained in operation until it was discontinued in 1995. The community was named for George A. Keeline, a cattleman. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Niobrara County, Wyoming
title: Keeline, Wyoming
